{{Infobox person | name = Kommer Damen | image = KommerDamen1984.jpg | image_size = | caption = Damen in 1984 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |72|2017|02|08|}}<ref name="Forbes" /> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Dutch | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = [[Gorinchem]], Netherlands | education = | alma mater = | occupation = | title = Chairman, [[Damen Shipyards]] | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = | boards = | salary = | networth = US$2.1 billion (February 2017)<ref name="Forbes" /> | spouse = married | parents = | children = 4 | relations = | website = }}
'''Kommer Damen''' (born 1944) is a Dutch [[billionaire]], and the chairman of the Netherlands-based [[Damen Shipyards]].<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web|title=The World's Billionaires: Kommer Damen|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/kommer-damen/|website=Forbes|accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=59741754&privcapId=8744739&previousCapId=8744739&previousTitle=Damen%20Shipyards%20Group%20N.V.|title=Kommer Damen: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|publisher=}}</ref>
Damen Shipyards was established in 1927 in the Dutch town of [[Hardinxveld-Giessendam]] by brothers Jan and Marinus Damen. In 1969 Jan Damen's son, Kommer took over, since when the company has built over 5,000 vessels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldmaritimenews.com/archives/152873/kommer-damen-wins-industry-leader-of-the-year-award/|title=Kommer Damen Wins Industry Leader of the Year Award|publisher=}}</ref>
Damen is married with four children and lives in [[Gorinchem]], Netherlands.<ref name="Forbes" />
