{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Moosa Bin Shamsher | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1945|10|15}} | birth_place = [[Faridpur Sadar Upazila|Faridpur]], [[Bengal Presidency]], [[British India]] (now [[Bangladesh]]) | residence = [[Gulshan, Dhaka]], Bangladesh | nationality = Bangladeshi | other_names = | alma_mater = [[Pacific Western University (Hawaii)]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Farndale |first=Nigel |author-link=Nigel Farndale |date=30 May 1998 |title=Man with the Golden Guns |newspaper=The Vancouver Sun |quote=Pacific Western University in the United States, establishes that it awarded Moosa a PhD in 1988 - after a correspondence course.}}</ref> | occupation = Chairman and Managing Director, DATCO Group | years_active = | known_for = |Net worth = 1.5 billion | spouse = Kaniz Fatema Chowdhury | children = 3 }} '''Moosa Bin Shamsher''' ({{lang-bn|মুসা বিন সামসের}}; born 15 October 1945) is a Bangladeshi businessman and the chairman and CEO of DATCO Group.
== Business == Moosa founded DATCO.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.datco-bd.com/group/ |title=Home |website=Datco |access-date=2011-07-21}}</ref>
== Media ==
=== DATCO group === Formed in 1975, Shamsher's business DATCO is now primarily engaged in the export of labour in the form of migrant rural farmers from Bangladesh to the booming construction industries in the Middle East.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/7985361.stm | work=BBC News | title=Dark side of the Dubai dream | date=6 April 2009}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=November 2016}}
===Offering donation=== During the UK [[United Kingdom general election, 1997|1997 general election]] it was reported that Moosa offered the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] and [[Tony Blair]] ₤5 million campaign donation. Although the party declined the donation the offer itself received a lot of media attention.<ref>{{cite news |last=Timmins |first=Nicholas |date=29 August 1994 |title=Labour rejects pounds 5m offer 'on principle' |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/labour-rejects-pounds-5m-offer-on-principle-1379387.html |location=London |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=2011-07-21}}</ref>
