{{Infobox officeholder | name = | office = | order = | image = | imagesize = | alt = | smallimage = <!--If this is specified, "image" should not be.--> | caption = | predecessor = | president = [[Nana Akuffo-Addo]] | successor = ''Incumbent'' | footnotes = | signature = | signature_alt = | party = [[New Patriotic Party]] | birthname = | birth_date = <!--{{birth year and age|1956}} or {{Birth date and age|1977|11|04}}--> | birth_place = [[Ghana]] | death_date = | death_place = | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | nationality = [[Ghanaian]] | otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> | spouse = | relations = | children = | residence = | alma_mater = | occupation = | profession = | cabinet = | committees = | portfolio = | blank1 = | data1 = | website = | honorific-prefix = | honorific-suffix = | term_start = | term_end = | religion = | blank2 = | data2 = | blank3 = | data3 = | blank4 = | data4 = | blank5 = | data5 = }}
'''Paa Kofi Ansong''' is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] biochemist, entrepreneur and businessman. He is the co-founder and chairman of venture capital group [[Investrade International]]. He serves on several Ghanaian boards including the director of Adehyeman Savings and Loans Company Ltd. He was appointed to the Council of State in February 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atlfmonline.com/home/24-ghana/1724-nana-addo-appoints-georgina-wood-to-council-of-state|title=Nana Addo appoints Georgina Wood to Council of State - atlfmonline|last=Hormeku|first=Rachel|website=www.atlfmonline.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-12-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/news/politics/full-list-nana-addo-appoints-adjiri-blankson-okudzeto-others-to-council-of-state-id6222727.html|title=Full List: Nana Addo appoints Adjiri Blankson, Okudzeto, others to Council of State|last=Taylor|first=Mildred Europa|access-date=2017-12-13|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Education and working life == Paa Kofi Ansong attended the [[University of Ghana]] and graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Biochemistry.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.adehyeman.com/details.cfm?prodcatID=1&tblNewsCatID=54&tblNewsID=134|title=Adehyeman Savings & loans|website=www.adehyeman.com|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref> After graduating from university, he traveled outside Ghana and initially worked as a Quality Control Officer with [[Boots Pharmacy]] in the United Kingdom.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=139078587&privcapId=129412883&previousCapId=129412883&previousTitle=Adehyeman%20Savings%20and%20Loans%20Company%20Ltd.|title=Paa Kofi Ansong: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref> Upon his return to Ghana, he co-founded a venture capital firm, Investrade International Company Limited, with his friend Kwadwo Amoafo in August 1993.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.invest61.com/About-Us.html|title=INVESTRADE INTERNATIONAL|website=www.invest61.com|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref> He now serves as the chairman of the firm. Due to his experience in private finance and management, he serves on many company boards across the country. They include Adehyeman Savings and Loans Company Ltd, St. Roses Secondary School in [[Akwatia]], Ghana National Procurement Agency and [[Abossey Okai]] Spare Parts Association.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0"/>
== Council of State == In February 2017 he was appointed to the council by President [[Nana Akufo-Addo|Nana Akuffo-Addo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ghananewsagency.org/politics/president-akufo-addo-appoints-11-to-council-of-state-113273|title=President Akufo-Addo appoints 11 to Council of State|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ghanabusinessnews.com/2017/03/01/nana-siriboe-ii-is-council-of-state-chairman/|title=Nana Siriboe II is Council of State Chairman - Ghana Business News|date=2017-03-01|work=Ghana Business News|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://presidency.gov.gh/index.php/2017/02/14/composition-of-the-council-of-state/|title=Composition of The Council Of State – The Presidency, Republic of Ghana|website=presidency.gov.gh|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ghanapa.com/okudzeto-13-others-appointed-as-council-of-state/|title=Okudzeto, 13 others appointed as Council of State|work=GhanaPa.com - The Goodness News Portal|access-date=2017-12-13|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/business/Okudzeto-13-others-appointed-by-Akufo-Addo-to-Council-of-State-510126|title=Okudzeto, 13 others appointed by Akufo-Addo to Council of State|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-13}}</ref> During the swearing-in ceremony held at The Flagstaff House, President Akuffo-Addo entreated the council to advise him well with the view to always propel Ghana to greater heights.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyguideafrica.com/council-state-elects-chairman/nana-otuo-siriboe-ii/|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II - Daily Guide Africa|website=dailyguideafrica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/politics/politics/201702/307190.php|title=Prez Akufo-Addo Swears In Council Of State|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ghananewsagency.org/politics/president-against-council-of-state-being-a-rubberstamp-113700|title=President against Council of State being a rubberstamp|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref> During the handing over ceremony of the sixth session of the council to the seventh, the outgoing council chair, [[John S. Nabila|Naa Prof. John S. Nabila]], advised the new house to give their best counsel to the new government to ensure that the country and all its citizens would live in prosperity and peace.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/local/social/201702/307237.php?storyid=100&|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II Elected Chairman of the Council of State|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref>
